Package com.mercedesbenz.carenquiry.service

Class DBCarService

java.lang.Object
com.mercedesbenz.carenquiry.service.DBCarService
@Service @Primary public class DBCarService extends Object
This class provides a service layer for the CarRepository class to perform various operations related to the Cars entity.

    • FindbyId

      Returns:

    • UpdateCar

      public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Cars> UpdateCar(@Valid @NonNull @RequestBody @Valid Cars cars, int id)
      This method is used to update the details of a car in the database with the given ID. It checks if the provided car name, car image, and car price are valid or not, and returns an error response if any of them are invalid. If all the details are valid, it updates the car details and returns a response with the updated car object and HTTP status OK. If the given ID does not exist in the database, it returns a response with an error message and HTTP status NOT_FOUND.
      Parameters:
      cars - the car object containing the updated details
      id - the ID of the car to be updated
      Returns:
      a response entity with the updated car object and HTTP status OK, or an error message and HTTP status NOT_FOUND or CONFLICT

    • deleteCar

      public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<String> deleteCar(int id)
      Deletes a car with the given ID from the database.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the car to delete
      Returns:
      a ResponseEntity with a success message and HTTP status code 200 if the car was deleted successfully, or a ResponseEntity with an error message and HTTP status code 404 if the car was not found in the database.
